name: Seattle Walking Photo Tour
description: Join a professional photographer on a hands-on photography walking tour through Seattle’s most picturesque spots. We’ll be covering close to 5 miles, so expect plenty of walking and opportunities to explore at a leisurely pace. And remember, it’s Seattle, so be prepared to get a little wet; the rain sometimes makes a guest appearance. Whether you’re new to DSLR photography or looking to refine your skills, this tour is designed to enhance your camera know-how and capture stunning images. As we explore iconic locations, I’ll provide personalized guidance, tips on composition, and help with camera settings. We’ll also take breaks at local cafes ☕️ or grab street food whenever available, making it a relaxed and enjoyable experience. I’ll be photographing alongside you and snapping professional shots of you at each spot. After the tour, you’ll receive access to download your images, making this a memorable and educational adventure.

name: Up to 14 Guests Private Skagit Valley Tulip Festival, Wine & Local Food Tour
description: This is a Private Small Group Tour for just you and your group!  As a proud official sponsor of the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival, we can't wait to take you to the region's best spring attraction!  Throughout April, the Skagit Valley's fields burst with a riot of color during the annual Tulip Festival.  While best known for the Tulip Festival, the Skagit Valley is also home to incredibly fresh ingredients and amazing food.  You’ll get “skip-the-line” access to both main tulip festival areas, enjoy a stop for lunch in the gorgeous seaside town of La Conner, and round out the afternoon with local wine tasting, hand-crafted cheeses and locally baked bread before returning to Seattle.

name: Craft Cocktail Gourmet Food Tour
description:
On this tour you will visit 3 of Seattle's premier restaurants and cocktail lounges and delight in the best food and drink in the city. 

Each location is specifically selected to represent a distinct characteristic of Seattle, from its history in the underground music scene, to its bounty of natural beauty and interconnectedness with nature, and to the sincerity in warmhearted hospitality of its people. 

Included in the price of your ticket is food and drink at all 3 locations (non-alcoholic options are available along with substitutions for dietary restrictions). 

A friendly guide will accompany you throughout, contributing context for each tasting and stories from their experience as a local. We also offer local-approved recommendations for whatever you're looking for around town. 

Everybody 21+ is welcome to join. There is about one third of a mile of walking, and elevators are available wherever there are stairs. 

We hope you'll join us!

review.name: Great Experience - We Highly Recommend
review.reviewBody: We greatly enjoyed this tour.  This is our second time experiencing the Craft Cocktail and Gourmet Food tour. Will was not only knowledgeable, he made it a completely different experience from the first and we got to see even more of Seattle than we might otherwise. Great work, Will. Thank you.

review.name: Delish!
review.reviewBody: The cocktails and appetizers at two of the restaurants (Mar Ket & Zig Zag) were excellent. The offerings at the Rabbit Box were OK. Will and Jade were terrific!

review.name: A great”taste” of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Will was informative, laid back and a lot of fun to be with. The drinks and food were all delicious, especially the lobster rolls at The Market. Food tours are always a great way to start to get a “taste” of the city!

review.name: Highly Recommended!
review.reviewBody: Absolutely incredible tour. Will the tour guide was personable and makes it casual but also full of information. I highly recommended this whether you’re a local or visiting from out of town. Thanks Will!

review.name: A must tour if you love a great bite and an amazing cocktail!
review.reviewBody: Fabulous tour!! We have lived in Seattle for over 20 years and have never done a food tour before. We did this for my husband's 50th and we had the best time. All the food bites were delicious and the cocktails were well crafted. We really enjoyed going to lesser known but amazing spots for a great bite and a cocktail. Our tour guide had great food expertise of not only the market spots but many places throughout Seattle. We left full, happy and ready to explore the list of places our guide recommended to go in the future. I highly recommend this experience it is worth every penny.

review.name: Happy Hour Review
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful guide, Jade, and she took us to some really neat places that we probably would never have ventured to on our own.  The drinks were delicious as was the food.  My only suggestion would be to make sure you're HUNGRY when you start the tour!!!

review.name: Brief review
review.reviewBody: Will did a good job picking places that were really yum and yet not what I may have tried on my own.

review.name: Great way to spend a couple hours!
review.reviewBody: We absolutely loved this tour. Our guide, Will, was so personable and made the experience enjoyable for everyone. Our party of four was joined by another couple, making the total of only six people in our group.  The amount of walking was very manageable, and the drinks and food were unique. We highly recommend this tour to anyone wanting a different experience in Seattle!

review.name: Fun time
review.reviewBody: Will was a wonderful guide!! Very knowledgeable and friendly!! He went out of his way to make our tour perfect!

review.name: Great time for social butterflies!
review.reviewBody: I went with my mom over memorial day weekend & had a great time. This was a smaller group, about 7 of us & the tour guide Will made 8. We got to learn a lot from the folks who worked at or owned the shops and go to places we may not have been able to find on our own. Will was the absolute best & my mom loved picking his brain about the best parts of Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Street Food Tour of South Lake Union- Area of Amazon Spheres

name: Street Food Tour of South Lake Union- Area of Amazon Spheres
description:
Experience the heart of Seattle’s tech center through the lens of a culinary walking tour. Over the last decade, this historical neighborhood has become home to the expansive Amazon and Google campuses—and, consequently, a vibrant street food scene that beckons both tech denizens and Seattleites who crave some of the city’s best noshes—from hand-rolled sourdough bagels at Rubinstein to Korean-Hawaiian fusion Marination to perfectly a balanced beverage from Rachel’s Ginger Beer to Middle Eastern mezze at Mamnoon Street. You stop at six different locations in South Lake Union for tastings and stories behind the distinctive local businesses.

Eat Seattle is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market PDA to operate tours in the Pike Place Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting tours within it’s properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity

review.name: Something Way Cooler than the Space Needle a Few Neighborhoods Over
review.reviewBody: This was so cool! It was our first time to Seattle and we are a family that likes to walk and explore different neighborhoods when we travel. We don't particularly love doing touristy things because we really want to know the culture of a place. This tour delivered that! Eric was an awesome, knowledgeable guide - and chef! We just loved it! Great information AND great food!

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Eric was great. We enjoyed all of the locations. We were able to see and learn about some Seattle history too.

review.name: Great for locals and out of town folks.
review.reviewBody: Chief Eric was fantastic. Found new favorite places in the area. Eric had found some fantastic places that I will be returning to.

review.name: Great food, highly recommend
review.reviewBody:
Very enjoyable experience! Chef Eric was courteous, knowledgeable, and entertaining, and he chose a great selection of food to try.

Both the quality and quantity of the food were excellent, would definitely recommend!

review.name: Great SLU time!
review.reviewBody: Eric was incredibly knowledgeable and friendly.  We had an amazing food experience and all of the restaurants were prepared for us in advance and had put bites ready!

review.name: Fabulous Food Tour
review.reviewBody: This food tour was both educational with regards to the history of Seattle as well as the food consumed. Eric was a fabulous tour guide. He provided interesting information while keeping us all laughing. I will look for other tours led by Chef Eric!

review.name: Very fun and unique experience!
review.reviewBody:
I purchased this tour as a unique Christmas gift for my foodie boyfriend and both he and I had an amazing time! ! Chef Eric made it incredibly easy to find and even secured us free parking which was a nice surprise! 

We began our tour with some incredible tamales and ended with one of the best macarons (and maybe one of the best desserts) I’ve ever had in my life! Eric was very professional and informative, but also funny and easygoing! He taught us about the history of some Seattle neighborhoods, the culture and science behind the corn that went into the tamales, the interesting bagel making process, and the thought behind different food pairings, etc. He had delicious samples ready for us at each stop and even made sure we had containers to take leftovers home! We were definitely full and happy by the end of the tour : )

I’ve never had an experience like this and I’m glad I took the leap and booked this tour! It is a great gift idea for anyone in your life that loves food or even to treat yourself! I’m already looking into Chef Eric’s other tours!

review.name: Great guide, great food.
review.reviewBody: We thoroughly enjoyed our tour around South Lake Union with Eric. He's personable, knowledgeable, and combines the history of the neighbourhood with detailed explanations about the venues and the food. It's always a bonus to have a chef leading the way because they're able to offer insight and answer questions about the process and procedure of the offerings. Highly recommend this particular tour as a slightly off the beaten path option over the ubiquitous Pike Place Market walks. Don't eat breakfast though - there's a lot of (delicious) food!

review.name: Street food tour exceeds expectations
review.reviewBody: The South Lake Union Street Food tour was incredible! It exceeded my expectations, so many different types of food. You should definitely come hungry and ready to eat.  It’s enough food for a large meal.   We had 2 types of tacos, an assortment of different flavor bagels, fried chicken, ginger beer and macarons.  Chef Eric was extremely knowledgeable and gave us tons of chef-y tips and tricks about cooking and the food we were eating.  Everything was super clean and moved quickly and easily through the city.  We are visiting from Los Angeles and really enjoy food and unique food experiences and this was the perfect thing to do on a rainy Seattle afternoon.

review.name: Food tour
review.reviewBody: Chef Noah was great! He made the tour fun, exciting, and engaging. The food was amazing and my wife and I had a wonderful time.
